  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 47a621783cb453147b01764dde5ed130, type: 3}
  m_Name: BecomingAFarmer
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::NPCDialogue
  dialogueLines:
  - Well now, there's a familiar face...
  - Or... familiar enough.
  - I'm Hal. I keep the market stocked around here.
  - Seeds, produce, bits and pieces folks tend to need.
  - Your grandmother had the finest garden I've ever seen.
  - Could grow just about anything in that soil.
  - Since you'll be staying at the cottage, you ought to know the basics too.
  - Here, take this...
  - A hoe for tilling soil, a watering can and some carrot seeds.
  - Plant the seeds in softened ground, give them water every day, and they'll sprout
    before long.
  - Bring me a grown carrot once it's ready. No rush.
  - Farming's best done patiently.
  - Carrots won't grow overnight.
  - Ah, now that's a healthy carrot. Not bad for a first harvest.
  - Your grandmother would've smiled seeing this.
  - Keep tending the garden and he land will start trusting you before long.
  - Every good harvest starts with a single seed. Folk tend to forget that.
